has become wearisome for you?

6
00:03:21,209 --> 00:03:23,677
Oh, no. No, no, my Lord Voldemort.

7
00:03:23,878 --> 00:03:25,106
I only meant...

8
00:03:25,279 --> 00:03:28,248
...perhaps if we were to do it
without the boy.

9
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:30,816
No! The boy is everything!

10
00:03:30,985 --> 00:03:34,512
It cannot be done without him.
And it will be done.

11
00:03:34,689 --> 00:03:37,351
Exactly as I said.

12
00:03:37,825 --> 00:03:41,454
- I will not disappoint you, my Lord.
- Good.

13
00:03:41,629 --> 00:03:44,689
First, gather our old comrades.

14
00:03:44,866 --> 00:03:47,096
Send them a sign.

15
00:03:58,813 --> 00:04:02,305
Nagini tells me
the old Muggle caretaker...

16
00:04:02,483 --> 00:04:06,180
...is standing just outside the door.

17
00:04:06,354 --> 00:04:11,656
Step aside, Wormtail,
so I can give our guest a proper greeting.

18
00:04:11,826 --> 00:04:13,657
Avada Kedavra!

19
00:04:18,700 --> 00:04:20,190
Harry.

20
00:04:20,935 --> 00:04:22,596
Harry!

21
00:04:23,905 --> 00:04:25,702
Are you all right?

22
00:04:26,407 --> 00:04:28,500
Hermione. Bad dream.

23
00:04:28,676 --> 00:04:32,043
- When did you get here?
- Just now. You?

24
00:04:32,213 --> 00:04:33,441
Last night.

25
00:04:33,614 --> 00:04:35,844
Wake up! Wake up, Ronald!

26
00:04:36,017 --> 00:04:37,279
Bloody hell.

27
00:04:37,452 --> 00:04:38,976
Honestly, get dressed.

28
00:04:39,721 --> 00:04:41,450
And don't go back to sleep.

29
00:04:41,622 --> 00:04:44,955
Come on, Ron!
Your mother says breakfast's ready!

30
00:04:51,632 --> 00:04:54,465
- Ron, where are we actually going?
- Don't know.

31
