- Hey, Dad. Where are we going?
- Haven't the foggiest.

32
00:04:58,372 --> 00:04:59,896
Keep up!

33
00:05:02,477 --> 00:05:04,308
Arthur!

34
00:05:04,479 --> 00:05:06,470
It's about time, son.

35
00:05:06,647 --> 00:05:11,016
Sorry, Amos. Some of us
had a bit of a sleepy start.

36
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:16,851
This is Amos Diggory, everyone.
Works with me at the Ministry.

37
00:05:17,058 --> 00:05:19,549
And this strapping young lad
must be Cedric, am I right?

38
00:05:19,727 --> 00:05:20,887
Yes, sir.

39
00:05:21,062 --> 00:05:22,723
This way.

40
00:05:24,465 --> 00:05:27,832
Merlin's beard!
You must be Harry Potter.

41
00:05:28,002 --> 00:05:30,732
- Yes, sir.
- Great, great pleasure.

42
00:05:30,905 --> 00:05:32,702
Pleasure to meet you too, sir.

43
00:05:35,343 --> 00:05:38,005
Yes, it's just over there.

44
00:05:40,281 --> 00:05:42,078
- Shall we?
- Oh, yeah.

45
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:43,444
We don't want to be late.

46
00:05:43,618 --> 00:05:47,748
Come on. Nearly there now.
Get yourself into a good position.

47
00:05:48,756 --> 00:05:51,088
Why are they all standing around
that manky old boot?

48
00:05:51,259 --> 00:05:53,750
- That isn't just any manky old boot.
- It's a Portkey.

49
00:05:53,928 --> 00:05:55,293
Time to go!

50
00:05:55,463 --> 00:05:57,055
What's a Portkey?

51
00:05:57,231 --> 00:06:01,258
- Ready! After three. One, two...
- Harry!

52
00:06:01,435 --> 00:06:02,527
...three!

53
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:14,707
Let go, kids!

54
00:06:14,882 --> 00:06:17,476
- What?!
- Let go!

55
00:06:29,530 --> 00:06:32,090
I'll bet that cleared your sinuses, eh?

56
00:06:33,167 --> 00:06:35,635
- Total shambles, as per usual.
- Thanks.

57
00:06:41,442 --> 00:06:43,569
Go on, look at that!

58
00:06:43,811 --> 00:06:48,339
Well, kids, welcome to
the Quidditch World Cup!

59
00:06:51,352 --> 00:06:53,980
Stay together! Keep up, girls!

60
00:06:55,523 --> 00:06:56,785
Look!

61
